Title: Aspects of BRST Quantization
Authors: J.W. van Holten
Comments: Lectures presented at the summerschool `Geometry and Topology in
  Physics', Rot a/d/ Rot (Germany), sept. 2001; 75 pages
Report-no: NIKHEF 01-018
\\
  BRST-methods provide elegant and powerful tools for the construction and
analysis of constrained systems, including models of particles, strings and
fields. These lectures provide an elementary introduction to the ideas,
illustrated with some important physical applications.
